---
import BaseHead from "../components/BaseHead.astro";
import LinkCallout from "../components/LinkCallout.astro";
import { Image } from "astro:assets";

import headerImg from "../images/2024-12-10_17.21.04.jpg";
import turtlemayImg from "../images/2024-12-11_13.47.56.jpg";
import hubImg from "../images/2024-12-11_13.45.54.jpg";

const UPDATED_DATE = new Date("Dec 12, 2024");

const MC_SERVER_VERSION = "1.21.3";
---
<head>
	<BaseHead />
	<title>Turtlemay's Minecraft Landing Page</title>
	<meta name="description" content="Turtlemay's Minecraft server landing page." />
</head>
<body>
	<div class="header-image">
		<Image src={headerImg} alt="" width={1920} />
	</div>
	<div class="page-header">
		<h1 class="heading">Turtlemay's Private Minecraft Server</h1>
		<div class="subheading" aria-hidden="true">
			<span>mc.trtl.in</span>
			<span class="dingbat" aria-hidden="true">❖</span>
			<span>{MC_SERVER_VERSION}</span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<main class="page-content">
		<section>
			<p>
				<samp>mc.trtl.in</samp>
				is my new small
				<a href="https://www.minecraft.net/en-us/store/minecraft-java-bedrock-edition-pc">Minecraft</a>
				server in the eastern US with survival and creative maps. Vanilla co-op survival is our foundation, complemented by a classic flat grass creative world.
			</p>
		</section>
		<section>
			<h2>Status</h2>
			<p>
				This server is brand new and ready to launch with fresh worlds. I am looking for a small group of players to start.
			</p>
			<Image src={hubImg} alt="" width={500} />
			<p>
				News will be posted to the private
				<a href="https://discord.com/">Discord</a>.
			</p>
		</section>
		<section>
			<h2>About Turtlemay</h2>
			<p>30M delivery driver with several hobbies.</p>
			<p>
				My Minecraft play style is cozy neighborhood builder. I like bringing home interesting materials and improving my tiny houses and farms.
			</p>
			<Image src={turtlemayImg} alt="" width={500} />
			<p>
				My Minecraft knowledge covers early beta through the "Combat Update" (2016), after which I stopped playing for many years. I will be learning about the new features as I go.
			</p>
			<p>I have lots of experience with servers.</p>
			<p>
				You can learn more about me at my
				<a href="https://www.turtlemay.us/">personal site</a>.
			</p>
			<aside aria-hidden="true">
				<LinkCallout text="My Website" href="https://www.turtlemay.us/" />
			</aside>
		</section>
		<section>
			<h2>Who should join?</h2>
			<p>
				You should join if you're an adult looking for some light co-op a few times a week or so. You must be older than 21, LGBTQ+ friendly, and preferably near the eastern United States. Any experience level is fine.
			</p>
			<p>
				Other than adding you to the group, I will not be acting as moderator or dungeon master. I am looking for friends and equals for a casual small community experience.
			</p>
			<p>
				Voice chat is not a priority but I would like to do some occasional group events.
			</p>
		</section>
		<section>
			<h2>How to apply</h2>
			<div class="apply-block">
				To request access, send an email to
				<span class="email">
					<samp>mc<span class="email-at"></span>trtl.in</samp>
				</span>
				and respond to the following:
				<ul class="prompts-list">
					<li>What is your experience with Minecraft?</li>
					<li>What is your general play style?</li>
					<li>Minecraft username</li>
				</ul>
				<p>
					Once whitelisted, I will add you on Discord so you can see other members and explore the server as you like.
				</p>
				<ul>
					<li>
						<b>Minecraft server address</b>: (whitelist only)<br/>
						<samp class="minecraft-address">mc.trtl.in</samp>
					</li>
					<li>
						<b>Discord server</b>: (invite only)<br/>
						You'll be added to Turtlemay's personal server.
					</li>
				</ul>
			</div>
		</section>
		<section class="server-rules">
			<h2>Server Rules</h2>
			<ul>
				<li>Be good to each other.</li>
			</ul>
			<div class="column-layout">
				<section>
					<h3 class="heading">Survival Worlds</h3>
					<ul>
						<li>Strict vanilla gameplay, normal difficulty, with no cheats or teleports (besides switching worlds).</li>
						<li>No unconsenting PVP, stealing, or griefing.</li>
					</ul>
				</section>
				<section>
					<h3 class="heading">Creative Worlds</h3>
					<ul>
						<li>Build what you want.</li>
						<li>Respect others' creations.</li>
					</ul>
				</section>
			</div>
		</section>
		<section>
			<h2>Technical Details</h2>
			<p>
				Just like the good old days, the server is hosted on an anemic low-end VPS with dual-core 2.10 GHz and 2G RAM, care of Cloudfanatic. Located in North Carolina. Performance is good enough for several players. Upgrades are a later discussion.
			</p>
			<p>
				We are using the latest Paper server software with minimal plugins besides MultiVerse and some creative tools.
			</p>
			<p>
				Test your ping with
				<samp>ping mc.trtl.in</samp>.
				You want well below 100ms or you might have a bad time.
			</p>
		</section>
		<hr />
	</main>
	<div class="updated-date">
		Updated:
		<date datetime={UPDATED_DATE.toISOString()} aria-description="page updated date">
			{UPDATED_DATE.toLocaleDateString("en-us", { year: "numeric", month: "short", day: "numeric"})}
		</date>
	</div>
</body>

<style>
body {
	margin: 0;
}

section > img {
	box-sizing: border-box;
	max-width: 100%;
	height: auto;
	padding: 6px;
	border: 1px solid #eee;
}

h2 {
	display: grid;
	grid-template-columns: auto 1fr;
	align-items: center;
	gap: 0.5em;
	&::after {
		content: "";
		border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;
	}
}

h3 {
	font-size: inherit;
	margin: 0;
}

ul {
	list-style: "❖";
	li {
		padding-left: 0.5em;
		margin-bottom: 0.5em;
	}
	li::marker {
		color: #ccc;
		font-weight: normal !important;
	}
}

hr {
	border: 0;
	border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;
	width: 4em;
	margin: 2em auto;
}

hr.dingbat {
	border: 0;
	width: unset;
	margin: 2em auto;
	text-align: center;
	&::before {
		font-size: 30px;
		content: "❦";
		color: #eee;
	}
}

samp {
	color: black;
	padding: 0 5px;
	background: #f5f5f5;
}

.email-at {
	&::before {
		content: "(at)";
	}
}

.minecraft-address {
	&::after {
		content: ":25565";
		color: #aaa;
	}
}

.header-image {
	background: black;
	color: white;
	display: flex;
	img {
		width: 100%;
		height: auto;
	}
}

.page-header {
	background: #050505;
	padding: 2em 1em;
	text-align: center;
	color: #fff;
	> :first-child {
		margin-top: 0;
	}
	> :last-child {
		margin-bottom: 0;
	}
	.heading {
		font: bold 30px "Roboto", sans-serif;
	}
	.subheading {
		font: 16px "Roboto", sans-serif;
		color: #666;
	}
	.dingbat {
		color: #333;
	}
}

.page-content {
	margin: 0 auto 10em;
	padding-left: var(--site-margin);
	padding-right: var(--site-margin);
	max-width: 800px;
	font: 16px "Roboto", sans-serif;
	line-height: 1.7;
	color: #222;
}

.page-content > section {
	margin: 1em 0 2em;
}

.page-content > :first-child {
	margin: 2em 0;
}

.updated-date {
	font: 14px "Roboto", sans-serif;
	text-align: center;
	color: #999;
	margin: 2em 0;
}

.page-content a {
	text-decoration: inherit;
	color: black;
	border-bottom: 2px solid #eee;
	transition-duration: 200ms;
	transition-property: filter;
	&:hover {
		filter: contrast(0.8);
	}
	&:active {
		filter: brightness(0.8);
	}
}

.apply-block {
	padding: 2em;
	background: #f5f5f5;
	border: 5px solid #eee;
	border-left: 0;
	border-right: 0;
	> :first-child {
		margin-top: 0;
	}
	samp {
		background: #fff;
	}
	.prompts-list {
		li {
			font-weight: bold;
		}
	}
}

.server-rules .column-layout {
	@media (width > 700px) {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
		gap: 1em;
		margin: 1.5em 0;
		.heading {
			display: grid;
			grid-template-columns: auto 1fr;
			align-items: center;
			gap: 1em;
			&::after {
				content: "";
				border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;
			}
		}
	}
}
</style>